\b\fs48 Typing Scripts\b0\fs30\par
\par
\b\f2 <font \ul FONT:STRING\ulnone >\b0\f0\par
\par
Change the Font used to type dialog. These Fonts are NOT the Fonts in your Stencyl Dashboard. They are the ones defined in extras/fonts.txt.\par
\par
\par
\b\f2 <color \ul COLOR\ulnone >\b0\f0\par
\par
Change the color of the font. -1 for default font color, or hexadecimal color code, such as (#ff0000) or (0xff0000) for pure red.\par
\par
\par
\b\f2 <typespeed \ul SPEED:FLOAT\ulnone >\b0\f0\par
\par
Change the type speed of the dialog. 0.1 would case a character to be typed ever 10th of a second.\par
\par
\par
\b\f2 <typesound \ul SOUND:STRING\ulnone >\par
or\par
<typesound [\ul SOUND:STRING\ulnone  ...]>\b0\f0\par
\par
Change the sound that plays when a character is typed, or set it to "none" for no sound.\par
Using the second tag, you can provide a list of sounds, one of which will be played at random when a character is typed.\par
\par
\par
\b\fs48 Tag Parameter Reference\b0\fs30\par
\par
Text is normally enclosed in quotes, but if you only have one word, it\rquote s okay to omit the quotes.\par
Ex: \i\f3 soup\i0\f0 , \i\f3\ldblquote soup\rdblquote\i0\f0 , and \i\f3\ldblquote good soup\rdblquote\i0\f0  each count as their own strings, but \i\f3 good soup\i0\f0  would count as two separate strings.\par
\par
ATTR:\par
"game" gameAttributeName:STRING\par
"scenebhv" behaviorName:STRING attributeName:STRING\par
"actorbhv" ACTOR behaviorName:STRING attributeName:STRING\par
"actor" ACTOR actorValueName:STRING\par
(The following option is available only for the "Messaging Scripts" extension)\par
"dialog" attrName:STRING\par
\par
A list is a pair of brackets with comma-separated values.\par
[Value1, Value2, Value3, [Value4, Is, A, List]]\par
\par
ACTOR: Name of Actor using the Actor Identifier. To name an actor, use the following code from anywhere: "GlobalActorID.set("Name of Actor", _actorAttribute);"\par
FONT: Name of Font resource in Stencyl or "none" for default\par
COLOR: Hexadecimal Int (0xffffff) or (#ffffff) or -1 for default\par
SOUND: Name of Sound resource in Stencyl or "none"\par
STRING: Text\par
FLOAT: Floating point number, such as .1\par
INT: Integer number.\par
DIALOG_CHUNK_ID: ID of Dialog (following the # in dialog file)\par
ANY: Can be a string, number, bool, or list.\par
IMAGE: Name of .png image (minus ".png" extension) stored in extras folder, or "none" for default.\par
